President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Christopher R. Beall as the Director of the AMTRAK Board of Directors. Beall is currently a Partner at Highstar Capital, specializing in transportation, environmental services, and energy sectors. He has previous experience as the Chief Financial Officer for Aslan Group and as an Associate in the Global Natural Resources division of Lehman Brothers Inc. Beall holds a B.S. in Mechanical Engineering from Oklahoma State University and an M.B.A. from Harvard.

Additionally, President Obama plans to nominate Lorne W. Craner as a Member of the Board of Directors of the Millennium Challenge Corporation. Craner is currently the President of the International Republican Institute (IRI) and previously served as Assistant Secretary for Democracy, Human Rights, and Labor at the Department of State. He has extensive experience in various roles, including Director of Asian Affairs for the National Security Council and Deputy Assistant Secretary of State for Legislative Affairs. Craner has a B.A. from Reed College and an M.A. from Georgetown University.